http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Tiger-dies-at-Bannerghata/article14002485.ece

An 18-year-old Tiger died due to ‘multi-organ failure’ in Bannerghatta Biological Park on Saturday.Park officials said Krishna, the male tiger at the popular safari section, had been taken for treatment earlier this week. “Post-mortem shows multi-organ failure. Kidneys, liver and gallbladder had failed due to old age,” park director Santosh Kumar said.Python deathsMeanwhile, park officials have finished the process of complete disinfection of the python cage after a series of deaths at the cage.Sources said four pythons had died in six months.